Preheat your oven to 200°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Halve the @red pepper{1}(halved, core removed and seeds removed) and thinly slice.

Pop the onion, beans, pepper and @Mexican style spice mix{1}(seasoned) on a large lined #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss together to combine. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until soft and coloured, ~{15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the top and bottom from the @carrot{1}(trimmed) and grate on a #coarse grater{}. Pop into a large #bowl{}. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}(root trimmed) and halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Add to the bowl with the carrot. Zest the @lime{1}(zested and chopped into wedges), then chop into wedges. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @low fat natural yoghurt{150%g}, lime zest and a pinch of salt and pepper. Set aside. Pop the grated cheese in another bowl and set aside. Add a squeeze of lime juice to the bowl with the lettuce and carrot, along with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Toss together. Add more lime juice to taste.

Two mins before the onion, beans and pepper are cooked, pop the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} on another baking tray and warm on the top shelf of your oven for ~{2%minutes}. Transfer the roasted veggies and beans to a bowl and get ready to serve.

Time to serve family style - put all the components on the table and let everyone build their own fajitas. Pile up the salad, roasted pepper, onion and beans, lime yoghurt, cheese and a couple of extra lime wedges for squeezing over. Roll and Enjoy!